### Electrolytic Purification of Copper

Copper is about 99% pure when it is first obtained from its ores. The main impurities are silver, platinum, iron, gold and zinc.

The impurities reduce the electrical conductivity of copper and so impure copper must be purified before being used e.g. for electrical wires. The purification of metals is known as _refining_.

