Since the \(E^{\Theta}\)(Cu\({}^{2+}\)/Cu) is less positive, Cu is preferentially oxidised at the anode. Thus Ag impurities will not be oxidised and they fall to the bottom as'sludge'.

Impurities with \(E^{\Theta}\) values less positive than Cu e.g. Zn

Zn\({}^{2+}\) + 2e\({}^{-}\) \(\rightleftharpoons\) Zn \(E^{\Theta}\) = -0.76 V

