Example: \({\rm Cu^{2+}}\)(aq) + 2e\({}^{-}\)\(\rightarrow\) Cu(s)

The greater quantity of electricity, **Q**, passed through the cell

\(\Rightarrow\) a greater amount of e\({}^{-}\) passed through

\(\Rightarrow\) a greater mass of Cu(s) deposited.

This can be achieved by using a **higher current** or passing the current through for a **longer** duration. Increasing the concentration of Cu\({}^{2+}\) will **not** result in a greater mass of Cu(s) deposited within the same duration.

